Peter Y. Solmssen: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 4:38 PM ET
Insurance

Company Overview of American International Group, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Peter Y. Solmssen  EVP - Legal, Compliance, Regulatory Affairs &  Government Affairs and General Counsel, American International Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships62--
Background

		Mr. Peter Y. Solmssen has been Executive Vice President of Legal, Compliance, Regulatory Affairs & Government Affairs and General Counsel at American International Group, Inc since October 18, 2016. Mr. Solmssen oversees the Global Legal, Compliance, Regulatory and Government Affairs functions. He also serves as a member of AIG's Executive Leadership Team and participate in all strategic and policy decisions affecting it's operations. He served as the Head of Corporate ... Legal & Compliance and Executive Vice President at Siemens Aktiengesellschaft (also known as Siemens AG) until December 31, 2013 and its General Counsel and Member of management board from October 1, 2007 to December 31, 2013 with responsibility for Siemens' businesses in the Americas. He served as the Acting Chief Compliance Officer of Siemens Aktiengesellschaft from May 2010 to June 2010. He served as a Member of the Managing Board at The Siemens Automation and Drives Group, Siemens Metering, Communications and Services. He served as General Counsel of GE Healthcare Limited since November 2002 and also served as its Executive Vice-president. He served as Vice President and General Counsel at GE Medical Systems, a General Electric Company since 2002. He was Attorney specializing in securities law at Ballard, Spahr, Andrews & Ingersoll and Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, USA since 1982. He served as Law Clerk at United States Federal District Court Judge Clarence C. Newcomer in the Federal District Court for the Eastern District of Pennsylvania since 1980. Before joining GE Healthcare, Mr. Solmssen served as Vice President and General Counsel at GE Advanced Materials (formerly, GE Plastics) from 1998 to November 2002. He served as Vice President and General Counsel of General Electric Company - GE Medical Systems, Waukesha, WI, USA since 2002. Before joining GE, he served as a Senior Partner in the law firm of Morgan, Lewis & Bockius since 1989. He was a Leader in Morgan, Lewis & Bockius's international and corporate practice. He served as the Chairman of Siemens Corporation until December 31, 2016 and is its Director. He serves as Vice Chairman of the German American Chamber of Commerce in New York and the Chairman of the 2004 United Way of Waukesha campaign. He served as a Director of Nokia Networks and Nokia Solutions and Networks Oy. He was Articles Editor of the law review of University of Pennsylvania. Mr. Solmssen received his AB in History and Literature from Harvard University, was a Knox Fellow (Scholarship program) at Oxford University and received his Law Degree from the University of Pennsylvania.Read Full Background




