Mr. Peter Y. Solmssen - American Conference Institute





















































Toggle navigation



























Home













			Mr. Peter Y. Solmssen		
General Counsel, Member of the Managing Board at Siemens AG
PETER Y. SOLMSSEN became the General Counsel and a Member of the Managing Board of Siemens AG on October 1, 2007.  As General Counsel, he is responsible for legal and compliance matters, a newly created position on the Managing Board at Siemens. His special responsibilities are the Americas.  Solmssen brings nearly three decades of international legal experience to the position.  He is a recognized expert in international merger and acquisitions and securities law.  Prior to joining Siemens, Solmssen was for five years Executive Vice President and General Counsel for GE Healthcare, one of the six operating units of General Electric Company, based in Chalfont St. Giles, UK.  While at GE Healthcare he led an industry-wide compliance initiative that culminated in a new code of conduct for diagnostic imaging vendors.  He joined GE in 1998 as Vice President and General Counsel of GE Plastics in Pittsfield, Massachusetts.  From 1989 to 1998, Solmssen was a senior partner in the law firm of Morgan, Lewis & Bockius LLP of Philadelphia.  He was in charge of the firm's Frankfurt am Main office, specializing in M&A and securities law.  One of his notable transactions was the listing of SAP AG on the New York Stock Exchange.  Solmssen started his career as an attorney at the law firm of Ballard, Spahr, Andrews & Ingersoll, in Philadelphia, from 1982 to 1989.  Before that he served as a law clerk for U.S. Federal District Court Judge Clarence C. Newcomer, from 1980 to 1982.  Solmssen received his J.D., cum laude from the University of Pennsylvania in Philadelphia, where he was Articles Editor of the University of Pennsylvania Law Review and his A.B. magna cum laude from Harvard University. He also studied law at Brasenose College, Oxford University, U.K., on a Knox Fellowship.  Solmssen was born on January 24, 1955 in Philadelphia.  He speaks fluent German.


 




 











